In the Good Friday prayers it may be remarked that Gem. in the prayer “pro christianissimo imperatore‚'' reads “respice ad Anglornm benignus imperium.'' The form for the Benedictzo Cerei is that commonly found, agreeing (except for a few slight variants) with Leofr. and the first of the two forms in (Mun). The lessons and prayers before the Benedictto Fontis agree with the order of Mur, not with the fuller order of Leofr. and (Mur.): but the tracts Cantemus domino and Vinea sacta est, which Mur. does not mention, are indicated in Gem.
